Title: Free Fermions at Finite Temperature: An Application of the
  Non-Commutative Algebra
Authors: S. M. de Souza, O. Rojas Santos, M. T. Thomaz
Comments: 14 pages, no figures
\\
  Charret et. al. applied the properties of the Grassmann generators to develop
a new method to calculate the coefficients of the high temperature expansion
of the grand canonical partition function of self-interacting fermionic models
in any d-dimensions (d>=1). The method explores the anti-commuting nature of
fermionic fields and avoids the calculation of the fermionic path integral. We
apply this new method to the relativistic free Dirac fermions and recover the
known results in the literature.
